children.subject: Budget constraints were definitely not restored entirely to normal, only partially.

Im like 17 on the waitlist.
From what I remember, on berkeley time the course usually expands to like 280 ish (which is like 60ish more people), however there might be some unknown forces that I cant really account for (such as budget constraints which were supposedly resumed to normal, but who knows). They usually would have expanded the course by now, but they havent, so im not sure if they will. 

Also i remember an earlier thread saying people drop the course a lot early cause they realize how heavy the courseload is, but berkeleytime data doesnt really support this. Theres always the 10% rule, and I think the class is at like 220 right now, so with that you would have a decent shot, but id wait it out a bit if I were you. It was also offered over summer this year, so it might be again next year.

history.content: Im currently 28 on the waitlist and I fear that I won't get off it. This is the last course I need to be good unit wise for next semester and every other CS class has a long wait list. Do a lot of people usually drop the course?
history.subject: What are my odds of getting into CS 184?
